<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="256" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,788,814]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Description.</emphasis>
Penis in side view with narrow, concave or almost straight ventral crest widened only basally and covered with small denticles (Figs. 62, 64, 66–68, 70). Male anal collar appendage blade-shaped, covered with minute spicules as in all other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Tishechkin" authorityYear="2017" box="[525,684,860,887]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
<emphasis box="[525,550,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[566,590,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[606,684,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (Figs. 65, 69, 71).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
According to the original description, the penis of this species has a strongly concave ventral crest (Fig. 62). Actually, the shape and width of the ventral crest vary even between males from the same sample (Figs. 64, 66–67). For this reason, distinction between 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Tishechkin" authorityYear="2017" box="[552,709,968,995]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
<emphasis box="[552,576,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[591,616,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[631,709,969,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[761,785,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1959" box="[791,933,968,995]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="estonica" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
(
<emphasis box="[800,817,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[840,933,969,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">estonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sometimes is difficult and their range boundaries in European 
<collectingCountry box="[354,429,1004,1030]" name="Russia" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Russia</collectingCountry>
and in 
<collectingCountry box="[512,643,1004,1030]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
are obscure.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="256" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1040,1066]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Biology.</emphasis>
“Ecologically, this species is apparently associated with sunny areas on sod-carbonate soils, where limestone reaches almost to the surface of the earth” (
<bibRefCitation author="Vilbaste, Yu. G." box="[761,988,1076,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" pagination="199 - 203" refId="ref14276" refString="Vilbaste, Yu. G. (1959) A new species of the genus Anaceratagallia Zachw. (Homoptera: Iassidae) from Estonia. Eesti NSV teaduste akadeemia toumetised, 8 (3), 199 - 203. [in Russian with Estonian and German summary]" type="journal article" year="1959">Vilbaste, 1959: 202</bibRefCitation>
). We collected this species from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Rumex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polygonales" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Rumex acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[279,438,1112,1139]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polygonales" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Polygonaceae</taxonomicName>
) on a sunny glade in a pine forest among sparse vegetation on sandy soil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1148,1174]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Calling signal.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014906320" collectingDate="1988-07-26" county="Signals" location="Beloozerskiy Town" municipality="Voskresensk Region" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Moscow">
<collectingCounty box="[384,466,1148,1174]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Signals</collectingCounty>
of two males from 
<collectingRegion box="[702,881,1148,1175]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Moscow Oblast</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingMunicipality box="[899,1134,1148,1174]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Voskresensk Region</collectingMunicipality>
, environs of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:76154D29AE59CF3AFF79FD92FD6AFA61:FB63AAE4AE59CF3AFAE6FBA8FF6EFB00" county="Signals" municipality="Voskresensk Region" name="Beloozerskiy Town" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" stateProvince="Moscow">Beloozerskiy Town</location>
, 
<collectedFrom box="[229,461,1184,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
on 
<taxonomicName box="[264,461,1184,1210]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Rumex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polygonales" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis box="[264,461,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Rumex acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</collectedFrom>
on the glade in pine forest, 
<date box="[773,926,1184,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" value="1988-07-26">
<collectingDate box="[773,926,1184,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" value="1988-07-26">26. VII. 1988</collectingDate>
</date>
, recording at 26 
<superScript attach="right" box="[1114,1142,1184,1210]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">oC</superScript>
) were investigated
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
The calling signal is a phrase lasting for about 10–20 s and consisting of two parts (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1272,1220,1246]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–93" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[205,1381,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-16@8.[192,1395,181,1874]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 80–93. Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) spp., calling signal oscillograms. 80–84― A. (A.) estonica, 85–93―A. (A.) chalchica. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “82–84” and “90–93”are given under the same numbers. 85, 90―male from Tyva, locality No. 1 in the list in calling signal description, 86, 91―male from Northern Buryatia, ibid., locality No. 2, 87–89, 92–93―male from Southern Buryatia, ibid., locality No. 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398494/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Figs. 80–84</figureCitation>
). The first part is a succession of syllables following each other with variable comparatively long intervals up to 2–3 s. Syllables in the second part have a more stable repetition period of 250–350 ms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="256" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1328,1354]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,446,1328,1354]" name="Estonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Estonia</collectingCountry>
, Northern half of European 
<collectingCountry box="[761,836,1328,1354]" name="Russia" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[850,948,1328,1354]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Moscow</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1002,1117,1328,1354]" country="Russia" name="Leningrad" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Leningrad</collectingRegion>
Oblasts), Northern, Central, and Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[290,424,1364,1390]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,1499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1400,1426]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">Remarks.</emphasis>
In our previous articles (
<bibRefCitation author="Tishechkin, D. Yu." box="[589,786,1400,1426]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" pagination="11 - 58" refId="ref14141" refString="Tishechkin, D. Yu. (2003) Vibrational communication in leafhoppers from Ulopides subfamilies group (Homoptera: Cicadellidae and Membracidae with notes on classification of higher taxa. Russian Entomological Journal, 12 (1), 11 - 58. Available from: https: // kmkjournals. com / upload / PDF / REJ / 12 / ent 12 _ 1 % 20011 _ 058 % 20 Tishechkin. pdf (accessed 15 th July 2020)" type="journal article" year="2003">Tishechkin, 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tishechkin, D. Yu." box="[796,854,1400,1426]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" pagination="50 - 60" refId="ref14223" refString="Tishechkin, D. Yu. (2017) On the taxonomy of Anaceratagallia Zachvatkin, 1946 (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae: Agalliinae) of Western Kyrgyzstan. Zootaxa, 4273 (1), 50 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4273.1.4" type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
) signal oscillograms of 
<emphasis box="[1118,1142,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1959" box="[1148,1289,1400,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="estonica" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
(
<emphasis box="[1157,1174,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1196,1289,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">estonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were erroneously presented under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Tishechkin" authorityYear="2017" box="[511,669,1436,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
<emphasis box="[511,535,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[551,568,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[591,669,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Tishechkin, D. Yu." box="[868,1073,1436,1462]" pageId="6" pageNumber="256" pagination="50 - 60" refId="ref14223" refString="Tishechkin, D. Yu. (2017) On the taxonomy of Anaceratagallia Zachvatkin, 1946 (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae: Agalliinae) of Western Kyrgyzstan. Zootaxa, 4273 (1), 50 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4273.1.4" type="journal article" year="2017">Tishechkin (2017)</bibRefCitation>
the drawings of genitalia of true 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Tishechkin" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,310,1472,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
<emphasis box="[151,176,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[192,209,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[232,310,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="256">venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Inner Tien Shan Mts. are given.
</paragraph>
